{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Covid bail outs for companies in exchange for carbon-reducing commitments.",
        "additional_details": "Covid-19 has presented us with empty shelves, personal tragedy and public conflict. A glimpse into a future we may face as a result of climate change. \r\n \r\nRescue packages to help the economy recover from the Covid-19 crisis present a major opportunity for our economy to make the urgent move away from fossil fuel dependency, to one that can grow sustainably and help limit global warming to 1.5\u00b0C above pre-industrial levels.",
        "background": "We call on the chancellor Rishi Sunak to grant public money only to companies which make firm, transparent, carbon-reducing commitments in line with the UN's IPCC recommendations.",
